      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The money held in escrow is managed by a neutral third party, often an escrow company or a title company, not your realtor. This entity acts as a guardian for the funds and documents, ensuring that neither party can access them until all the conditions of the sale are met. This way, you can be confident that the money will be released to the seller only when it's time to close the deal, and the documents will be exchanged securely. It's a trustworthy system that keeps the transaction fair for both you and the seller.",
