    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. so if this third party is basically just guarding the money until everything is ready, are there any specific risks or things i should watch out for with these companies? like how do I know they won't just lose the money or something?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "While it's true that any third party can potentially make mistakes, reputable escrow companies and title companies are heavily regulated and have a strong track record. To minimize risks, you can do a few things: check their credentials and history, read reviews, and compare services. It's also a good idea to work with a reputable real estate attorney who can guide you through the process and help you understand the protections in place. Moreover, your lender will usually work with a trusted escrow company, which adds an extra layer of security. Just be sure to ask plenty of questions and do your due diligence before choosing an escrow company.",
